(12, 'TIM Wallet', 'smartlife', 'TIM', 'Choose payment cards of Intesa Sanpaolo, BNL or Mediolanum: pay is simple and convenient!', '<h2> By TIM Wallet you can use your smartphone to pay for all authorized shops </h2>\r\n<H3> SAFE </h3><P>The details of your credit card or debit card are stored confidentially and protected on TIMcard</P> <h3> QUICK AND EASY </h3><P>Just a touch to select the card with which to make your purchases</P> <h3> COMFORTABLE </h3><P>Leave your wallet at home and use the smartphone to have on hand your cards</P>', '<Div class = "col-xs-12 col-sm-12"><! - What are smartphones compatible with NFC services? -><H3> What are smartphones compatible with NFC services?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>TIM Wallet is compatible with all SIM BASED NFC smartphones, terminals that can read the information stored on the SIM with the security required by banks and payment networks. The list of NFC smartphones, tested and released, is constantly changing. Enabling other phones require appropriate security checks not only by TIM but also from our partners. See the updated list of<a href="pagamenti.html#terminaliAbilitati" class="link"> </a> enabled terminals.</P></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>To date the application TIM Wallet is not available for iOS and Windows Phone platform.</P></Div><! - <Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>If you have a smartphone belonging to the list of authorized terminals, but the application indicates an incompatibility, you can deepen the problem by writing to <a class="mail" href="mailto:timwallet@telecomitalia.it"> timwallet@telecomitalia.it . </a> and indicating:</P><Ul class = "innerList"> <em> * </em> The IMEI smartphone on which his SIM you entered (you can get on the phone by dialing <em> * # 06 # </em>).  <em> * </em> in Settings -> About Phone-> Software information or the version of the operating system or the make and model of phone or version of Android or kernel version or build number or alternatively the screen shoots of the page .  <em> * </em> If your smartphone is Samsung, the codes displayed on your phone by dialing <em> * # 1234 # </em>.  <em> * </em> If you receive an error message, you can report the information received or alternatively send us a screenshot of the page. </Ul><Ul class = "innerList"><Em> * </em> Make and model of the smartphone<Em> * </em> The IMEI smartphone (you can get on the phone by dialing <em> * # 06 # </em>).<Em> * </em> The information on the phone''s software that you can find under Settings -> About Phone. They are fine version of Android or kernel version or build number or alternatively the screenshot of the page<Em> * </em> If your smartphone is Samsung, the codes are displayed on the phone by dialing <em> * # 1234 # </em><Em> * </em> If you receive an error message, you can report the information received or alternatively send us a screenshot of the page</Ul></Div> -><! - What is NFC? -><H3> What is NFC?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>NFC (Near Field Communication) is a technology that provides short-range wireless connectivity. The NFC allows the "interview" safely between your phone and a POS enabled during a contactless payment transaction or those transactions that occur simply approaching the payment instrument (a card or, as in our case, a phone) to the POS, without the need for insertion inside the player. NFC technology provides encrypted transactions according to the security requirements of banks and payment networks. The details of your credit card details are securely stored on your SIM. This particular method of payment is usually defined Mobile Proximity Payment.</P></Div><! - The NFC technology is safe? -><H3> The NFC technology is safe?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P> The payments via NFC technology guarantee encrypted transactions according to the security requirements of banks and payment networks. </P></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><Ul class = "innerList">Indeed :<Ul class = "innerList"> It is impossible to pay "by mistake": the payment will only work if your smartphone is approached a few centimeters from the player after you typed the amount on the POS.  There is no risk of double-charging: although it touches more than once the reader with your Smartphone will always recorded one transaction. </Ul></Ul></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><Ul class = "innerList">In particular, for greater safety recalls of:<Ul class = "innerList"> Always set the block with the screen of your smartphone PIN to not let anyone, even in case of theft of your phone, you use the NFC payment functionality. If you want you can also set the TIM Wallet PIN.  Never save your PIN in your Smartphone in your payment card to not let anyone, even in case of theft of your phone, to make NFC payments above 25 â‚¬. </Ul></Ul></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><Ul class = "innerList">To know in detail all the risks, please consult the fact sheet available on the website of the banks.</Ul></Div><! - I forgot / lost my PIN TIM Wallet or the PIN of the Payment Card. What should I do? -><H3> I forgot / lost my PIN TIM Wallet or the PIN of the Payment Card. What should I do?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>In case I forgot / lost the TIM Wallet PIN (required optionally opening of the TIM Wallet) and I could not retrieve it with the question / secret answer, please ask for the PIN reset on the site <a href = "https: //www.tim.it/assistenza/moduli "target =" _blank "> https://www.tim.it/assistenza/moduli </a> or, if you are a business customer, contact the usual channels of access to Business Customer service.</P></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>In case I forgot / lost my PIN payment card or the login credentials to the app of the Bank, please contact the customer service of your bank.</P></Div><! - Someone stole / I lost my phone! What should I do? -><H3> They stole / I lost my phone! What should I do?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>Call 119 to lock the SIM and the phone, providing his IMEI code. If you want to reactivate the TIM Wallet service, went to one of TIM stores authorized to request a new TIM Card NFC, check with your bank or in the terms and conditions of service as reactivate NFC services.</P></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>If you''ve enabled a payment card, contact the customer service of your bank to block the card.</P></Div><! - Someone stole / I lost my phone! I run that risk? -><! - <H3> They stole / I lost my phone! I run that risk?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>No, if someone tries to make operations for amounts of more than 25 â‚¬. These operations can be performed only and exclusively by entering the PIN code of your card for payment.</P></Div><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>Amounts less than â‚¬ 25, however, are active monitoring systems on transactions that signal using suspicions of the Charter, blocking its operation. In any case, as soon as you notice the theft or loss call 119 to lock the SIM card and the customer service of your bank to block the card.</P></Div> -><! - I can not make the payment! What can I do? -><H3> I can not make the payment! What can I do?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>First, make sure you have the SIM NFC, to have an NFC compatible smartphone, active TIM Wallet and APP of the active Bank. Make sure you have requested activation of the payment service to your bank and the payment card you have enough credits. Then check that the date and time of your phone are correct. If they are, please contact Customer Service on your bank</P></Div><! - If you step near a POS, there is a risk that it can pay the bill of another? -><H3> If you step near a POS, there is a risk that it can pay the bill of another?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>It is impossible to pay "by mistake" with the paper: to make a payment transaction must be selected before the payment card from the App TIM Wallet or the Bank. Once selected, you have 1 minute of time about to make the payment, then the application is automatically deactivated.</P></Div><! - How do I further increase the security level of the Charter? -><H3> How can I further increase the security level of the Charter?</H3><Div class = "answer animated flipInX"><P>We recommend that you always set the lock screen PIN with your smartphone to not let anyone, even in case of theft of your phone, you use the NFC payment functionality. If you want you can also set the TIM Wallet PIN.</P></Div></Div>', 4, 'phone-card-pagamenti.png', 'phone-card-pagamenti.png', NULL, NULL, 0);

